{
  "texts": [
    "For those graphs with X-node features, the output of the layer 1 GCN is the feature vector learned by the layer 1 graph convolutional layer",
    "Where W (0) is the weight matrix of the 1st graph convolution layer; Relu(•) is the activation function of the convolutional layer of the 1st layer of the graph.",
    "The final feature vector is obtained by putting the feature vector learned by the GCN in layer 1 into layer 2:",
    "Finally, the learned node features are input to the fully connected layer for classification to get the prediction results:",
    "Where sof tmax(•) is the classification function; F C(•)is the fully connected layer output."
  ]
}